de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result.fusion.type

Class TypeFusion

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result.fusion.type.TypeFusion

  • public class TypeFusion
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is responsible for fusing type metadata information. Therefore the metadata information corresponding to every URI are added to a subgroup which covers objects with a similar URI. For every subgroup a common value for format and language are determined and finally appended to the scopeResource.
    Since:
    06.03.2014
    Author:
    Sebastian Schulz
    See Also:
    TypeFusion(Model, String), add(ParsedMetadata), checkForSubgroup(String), fuse(), createSubgroupProperty(TypeSubgroup), #addNoTypeProperty(String)

    • Method Detail

      • add

        public void add(ParsedMetadata singleMetadata)
        This method adds the type metadata information to an existing TypeSubgroup or adds a new one to the subgroups ArrayList. Hence the MatchingHelper.getSubUri(URI) method is called to retrieve the first part of the URI of the given ParsedMetadata object. Notice that this method performs the actual fusion process in this case.
        Parameters:
        singleMetadata - - a ParsedMetadata object which contains the type information.

      • checkForSubgroup

        private int checkForSubgroup(java.lang.String subUri)
        This method iterates over the ArrayList of subgroups and checks if the given subUri is the same as the one stored in the subgroup.
        Parameters:
        subUri - - a String representation of the URI of the current ParsedMetadata object.
        Returns:
        matchingIndex - an int value. The index of the first subgroup which sharedUri equals to the given subUri, if no subgroup matches '-1' is returned.

      • fuse

        public void fuse()
        This method calls the createSubgroupProperty(TypeSubgroup) for every subgroup to create the type fusion resouce.

      • createSubgroupProperty

        private void createSubgroupProperty(TypeSubgroup subgroup)
        This method adds the subgroup property to the scopeResource. If the subgroup has a format a formats property is added and if it has a defined language a language a language property is appended.
        Parameters:
        subgroup - - a TypeSubgroup object.

      • addSingleNoTypeProperties

        private void addSingleNoTypeProperties(NoMetadataObject noMetadata)
        This method creates a panda:NoMetadata property to the scopeResource and puts the "link" to the objects URI to it.
        Parameters:
        noMetadata - - a NoMetadataObject all URI withou metadata.
